commit.message:
thread_element_unique_thread(): loudly warn on resets.

Forgot to clear the TID in thread_element_mark_reusable_locked().

Now that this is fixed, it makes sense to loudly warn if we ever have to
reset the TID of a thread element.

Also added debugging assertions, protected by the optional THREAD_DEBUG
define, to make sure the TID field is always consistent in the
thread_element object.

mutex_log_error(): also display STID for self.

We need to ensure thread_current() and thread_self() point to the same
thread ID, hence emphasize it in the log message.  If different, then
the root cause of the crash lies in the thread layer, not in the mutex
locking logic!
mutex_not_owned(): trace owner if mutex is locked.
Beware that "te->ptid" is not always a scalar value.
Test whether directory exists before creating it.
Add braces to avoid compiler warning.
Remap g_memdup() to g_memdup2(), if available.
Fixed wrong code identation, causing warnings now.
Remove usage of GNU TLS deprecated functions.

Force supervisor to quit if child gets a SIGKILL.

It could be the user killing a stuck process, or the kernel raising an
OOM kill because the process uses too much memory.  Either way, this is
an abnormal condition and it is best to avoid automatically restarting a
new child.
Adding build packages to correct start errors
